President Donald Trump has announced his first wave of candidates for United States Attorney positions. These individuals have been nominated to serve as United States Attorneys in various districts across the country. The candidates include D. Michael Dunavant, Louis V. Franklin Sr., Justin E. Herdman, John W. Huber, Brian J. Kuester, Jessie K. Liu, Richard W. Moore, and Jay E. Town. Each candidate has a background in law enforcement or prosecution and, if confirmed, will serve as the chief federal law enforcement officer in their respective districts.